4 EPIGRAMMATA.

LIII. AD ILLUSTREM LADERDELIAE COMITEM.

Non mihi sunt, rubro quae mittit ab aequore Tethys, Vel niger in viridi quae legit Indus aqua. Haec tibi, quae Phoebi sacris e fontibus hausi, Dona, Laderdeli, quantulacunque fero. Accipe Pierias, et, si vacat, inspice gerras; Hora sat est, oculo si properante legis. Alitis armigeri proles generosa putatur, Si qua potest Phoebi nobile ferre iubar. . Tu quoque Phoebeos, quo par est lumine, fetus Adspiciens, generis da documenta tui. 10 Heroo sic te prognatum sanguine, magno Nec Metellano degenerasse, probes. ART. IONST.

7. Alitis armigeri.] The eagle, as bearing the thunderbolt of Jove.

12. Metellano.] Not the famous william of this family, the secretary of Queen Mary's time, but the earl's father, John, the chancellor of James VI.’s time. As “joannes Metellanus‚'’ he has a niche as a poet in the ‘⁴ Delitiae‚” and a place in the Scottish peerage as the first Lord Maitland of Thirlstane (1590, died 1595).
